Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.18,0:00:13.70,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,This is Code Papillon!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.43,0:00:16.76,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Midsummer's Knights, do you copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.76,0:00:18.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Code Papillon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.91,0:00:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.38,0:00:24.49,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,This is Manatsu.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.49,0:00:25.92,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Do you copy? Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.09,0:00:31.23,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.23,0:00:32.89,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,We've got communication back.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.89,0:00:34.43,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Is everyone safe, Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.31,0:00:37.14,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,An unknown group attacked us,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.14,0:00:39.24,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,and the Nebula was immobilized.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.84,0:00:42.22,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But Teppei and Hana are safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.60,0:00:46.56,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We're heading for Australia Central Command...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.56,0:00:50.32,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Were you ambushed by Globe \Nunmanned weapons or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.69,0:00:54.08,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,In Australia, Salty Dog has a lot of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.08,0:00:56.12,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Central Command will be dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.12,0:00:57.26,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,So we have a new plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.26,0:00:58.78,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sending the data now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.68,0:01:02.93,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,To your north is the Carpentaria base.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.58,0:01:06.19,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's relatively undefended,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.19,0:01:08.47,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,but it has a newly deployed heavy transport craft.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.47,0:01:10.17,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,The ekranoplan {\i1}Bravnik{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.56,0:01:13.51,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,If you're familiar with it, we can skip \Nthe instruction manual, Teppei.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.01,0:01:15.02,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.02,0:01:17.96,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the activation codes to me and my magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.96,0:01:19.22,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.22,0:01:21.61,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,If you do something like that inside a base,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.61,0:01:23.76,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,it'll give them a reason to shoot you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.28,0:01:25.68,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The risk is too great!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.35,0:01:28.90,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.27,0:01:33.57,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I've hacked Central Command's main \Ncomputer, and knocked it offline.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.24,0:01:39.29,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.06,0:01:42.19,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I hadn't heard that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.65,0:01:44.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to pretend I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.16,0:01:46.55,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.55,0:01:49.50,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think I'm finished yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.50,0:01:52.46,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,If they want a fight, they'll get one!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.46,0:01:55.01,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you out in every way I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.01,0:01:56.22,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.73,0:01:57.63,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.14,0:02:02.64,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Commander, the Midsummer's Knights \Nwill now return to Tanegashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.98,0:02:04.02,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.02,0:02:04.94,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.64,0:02:07.14,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Akari.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.79,0:02:09.13,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.59,0:02:12.31,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to thank me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.31,0:02:14.05,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Akari...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.52,0:02:17.64,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Governor Yomatsuri told me—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.64,0:02:18.89,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.15,0:02:23.61,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell me when you come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.13,0:02:26.08,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.37,0:02:32.86,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, she's really begun to smile a lot more.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.59,0:02:37.55,Default - flashback,D,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.14,0:02:44.65,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,So it's you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.23,0:02:52.85,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Just be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.25,0:02:55.31,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.31,0:02:56.78,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.52,0:03:01.85,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It's thanks to Daichi and the others
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.38,0:03:04.15,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,that she can smile like that now, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.78,0:04:44.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The commander will be heading over there—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.13,0:04:52.17,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It was easy to get in with their systems down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.17,0:04:54.02,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Akari's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.64,0:05:02.25,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,That's a magical girl for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.40,0:05:13.20,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.86,0:05:16.04,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Why is the {\i1}Bravnik{\i0} leaving its hangar?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.35,0:05:20.00,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.26,0:05:32.77,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Australia Central Command and \Nits peripheral bases have had
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.12,0:05:37.23,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,their main systems hacked, \Nand have been down for nearly an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.58,0:05:40.38,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The computers are just now coming back online.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.66,0:05:46.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,They took advantage of the chaos \Nto steal the ekranoplan {\i1}Bravnik{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.65,0:05:49.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,and are already heading to Tanegashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.20,0:05:55.56,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It will take about ninety minutes to \Nget the Sarama Engine online.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.08,0:05:58.48,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Once it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.48,0:06:03.55,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,we'll be able to stop them before \Nthey reach Tanegashima.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.76,0:06:06.67,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Pillaging and running...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.40,0:06:09.64,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,I feel kind of like a pirate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.16,0:06:12.10,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Pirate Captain Earth, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.10,0:06:13.94,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.06,0:06:17.14,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,This is fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.27,0:06:25.28,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Your Smile Means Everything
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.59,0:06:30.20,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I have something to do today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.79,0:06:33.13,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Leave tomorrow night open.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.13,0:06:36.33,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I'm busy tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.76,0:06:38.52,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the day after?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.03,0:06:47.13,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.56,0:06:49.26,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,The day after won't work, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.94,0:06:55.93,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,So it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.40,0:06:57.39,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I've been dumped.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.96,0:07:07.07,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.52,0:07:09.66,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done playing games.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.66,0:07:12.64,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have Puck find us an area
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.64,0:07:17.08,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,where we can have Siren-sama collect \Nhigh-density libido for an all-out attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.81,0:07:19.50,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.32,0:07:23.63,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you interested in this avatar's body?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.30,0:07:25.46,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.53,0:07:31.63,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,You have no libido...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.28,0:07:34.85,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.66,0:07:39.56,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to pursue the three \Nof them with the Sarama Engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.92,0:07:41.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The Sarama Engine?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.42,0:07:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.36,0:07:47.19,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,An unmanned Impacter developed \Nprimarily by the Ark Faction,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.19,0:07:48.73,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,just like Cerberus.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.19,0:07:52.45,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,It's much more mobile than its size would suggest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.45,0:07:56.41,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,And it's equipped with smaller attack units.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.09,0:07:59.12,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,These specs look tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.66,0:08:03.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But once the {\i1}Bravnik{\i0} enters \NJapan's air defense zone,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.27,0:08:07.07,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,the enemy won't be able to touch it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.07,0:08:08.11,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.28,0:08:11.67,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it'll be that easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.45,0:08:17.46,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,We were right to send Salty Dog's observer back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.01,0:08:20.31,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.74,0:08:22.85,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,She probably thought that if she stayed,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.57,0:08:28.02,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,she'd be arrested for her attempt \Nto kidnap Hana Mutou.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.42,0:08:31.74,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,You're using the Sarama Engine?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.08,0:08:35.32,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Won't that bring in the JSDF Air Force?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.32,0:08:36.03,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.99,0:08:39.79,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.79,0:08:43.95,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, tell me what's \Ngoing on at the Tanegashima base.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.95,0:08:44.75,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.34,0:08:46.50,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,They're a tough nut to crack.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.31,0:08:50.03,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Organizations run by older people
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.03,0:08:53.40,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,tend to be experienced, knowledgeable, and careful,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.40,0:08:57.05,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,but too cautious to make any serious moves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.82,0:09:01.79,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,And organizations composed of \Nthe young have a lot of energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.79,0:09:05.23,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,but tend to lose control and destroy themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.73,0:09:10.11,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But when the young and old work \Ntogether with mutual respect,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.11,0:09:12.57,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,they make a strong team.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.85,0:09:16.66,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Tanegashima has that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.18,0:09:17.90,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.57,0:09:20.87,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.37,0:09:23.60,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we can't underestimate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.20,0:09:28.78,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,But we need Hana Mutou, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.78,0:09:29.59,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.01,0:09:33.55,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,But even if we do acquire Hana Mutou,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.22,0:09:37.80,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,I can't imagine she'll do what we ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.80,0:09:39.01,Default,Gi,0000,0000,0000,,Over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.01,0:09:41.97,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Once we have her, we'll make it work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.80,0:09:45.85,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,She has a teenage girl's mentality.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.34,0:09:49.67,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,They're willing to do anything it takes now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.93,0:09:59.99,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,They need Hana that badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.99,0:10:03.31,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,They need her power to operate the{\i0} Blume.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.62,0:10:09.88,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,Science Chief, thanks to your efforts,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.88,0:10:12.22,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,we learned where that spaceship came from,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.22,0:10:15.42,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,and about the dangers our planet faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.76,0:10:21.89,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,No, our technology couldn't \Neven get inside that ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.58,0:10:28.20,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,But fortunately, the entrainment analysis \Ntechnology I developed allowed us
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.20,0:10:32.86,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,to successfully communicate with \Nthe intelligent life form inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.63,0:10:35.09,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.01,0:10:37.49,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,Science Chief,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.07,0:10:42.97,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,is that young girl the intelligent life \Nyou've been communicating with?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.74,0:10:47.45,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,She looks like a girl... Is it her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.85,0:10:50.10,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,From my communications with her,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.10,0:10:55.17,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,I was certain that she was some kind of \Nbiological part of that spaceship.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.73,0:10:59.46,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,Since I've been speaking to her, \Nit seems natural to me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.46,0:11:01.93,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,that I've been speaking to \Nsomething that looks like a girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.91,0:11:06.33,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,No, that is a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.90,0:11:11.69,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,And she's terribly afraid of going \Nback inside that spaceship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.54,0:11:18.69,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, she can't leave the ship on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.46,0:11:24.94,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,But, Science Chief, why was Daichi Manatsu alone
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.60,0:11:28.28,Default - flashback,N,0000,0000,0000,,able to bring her out of the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.81,0:11:35.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I've calculated the time when the \NSarama will reach the {\i1}Bravnik{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.75,0:11:38.17,Default,20,0000,0000,0000,,20:25 JST.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.96,0:11:41.47,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you come home!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.67,0:11:44.54,Default - italics,N,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of this planet's future!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.94,0:11:48.63,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I have a body,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.63,0:11:51.02,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,I'm finding there are many things I didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.74,0:11:56.58,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Peter Westvillage, Science Chief \Nof Globe's Tanegashima base,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.58,0:11:59.48,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,has sent an e-mail to Masaki Kube.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.79,0:12:02.03,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Peter Westvillage...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.03,0:12:07.26,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,For a short time, he was our \Ncompany's science advisor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.26,0:12:12.15,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Is he sounding us out about \Nthe Machine Goodfellows?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.15,0:12:13.76,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,After the Kanda incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.76,0:12:17.81,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,our company ostensibly has nothing \Nto do with the Machine Goodfellows.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.51,0:12:20.32,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,He won't find out about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.32,0:12:21.58,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,No,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.58,0:12:27.55,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,he is asking for Masaki Kube's opinion \Nabout a scientific matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.55,0:12:29.68,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,What does he want to ask me about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.38,0:12:33.63,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Eternal life, apparently.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.04,0:12:36.27,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, isn't that interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.77,0:12:41.82,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,"If you had eternal life, how would \Nit change the way you thought?"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.32,0:12:44.74,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,But why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.10,0:12:49.29,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Macbeth currently possesses the world's \Nmost advanced machine intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.29,0:12:51.58,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,That is, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.58,0:12:55.23,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,And Masaki Kube is the one who \Ndeals with me the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.87,0:12:58.51,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Machine intelligence differs \Nfundamentally from humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.51,0:13:00.58,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,It has no biological lifespan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.06,0:13:04.34,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,It seems he wants to know
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.34,0:13:10.18,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,how this machine intelligence regards \Nits own life, its eternal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.13,0:13:13.36,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, if you have eternal life,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.36,0:13:17.65,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,the next thing you need is infinite energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.98,0:13:22.71,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,The theory that the Livlasters were \Nextradimensional life forms
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.71,0:13:24.19,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,that took the shape of a gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.19,0:13:28.51,Default,K,0000,0000,0000,,Peter Westvillage was the one \Nwho wrote the report.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.51,0:13:32.54,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,If those guns have a will of their own,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.15,0:13:37.00,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps they are the ones \Ntrying to take over the galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.50,0:13:40.75,Default,P,0000,0000,0000,,My true enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.73,0:13:48.43,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,They're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.26,0:13:54.60,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, they'll catch up to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.02,0:14:11.87,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We're always cutting it close...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.38,0:14:14.37,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,There are only two kinds of "close."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.80,0:14:17.71,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,"Close, but out" and "close, but safe."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.40,0:14:19.41,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.11,0:14:21.19,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure we'll get home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.73,0:14:40.19,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't easy being a pirate, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.79,0:14:48.09,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,In the distant past...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.30,0:14:54.10,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,I was in a world where everything \Nwas veiled by darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.60,0:14:59.79,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,They created me to fire the Livlaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.89,0:15:04.63,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.84,0:15:07.93,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,Darkness surrounded me on all sides,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.47,0:15:13.30,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,and the only thing they wanted \Nme to do was to fire that gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.72,0:15:21.59,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't even sure if I wanted to give \Nthem what they desired or not...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.71,0:15:27.03,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,But then, I thought I saw a light.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.55,0:15:33.95,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,It felt like someone's voice calling to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.70,0:15:38.54,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that I needed to meet that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.36,0:15:41.25,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,That I wanted to meet that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.99,0:15:44.76,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,So I ran toward the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.86,0:15:51.85,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.91,0:15:54.37,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,I found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.22,0:15:59.81,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,Is it you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.52,0:16:05.77,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,No, that isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.24,0:16:09.72,Default - italics,H,0000,0000,0000,,You found me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.06,0:16:20.69,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.66,0:16:23.25,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to the Flare Engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.57,0:16:25.13,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You're going?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.99,0:16:27.84,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.84,0:16:33.05,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.50,0:16:34.06,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.33,0:16:36.23,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.38,0:16:43.10,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Both craft have entered Japan's air defense zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.66,0:16:44.94,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Is the Air Force scrambling?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.39,0:16:46.31,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,There's no report of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.97,0:16:50.03,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It seems Salty Dog is pulling \Nstrings behind the scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.13,0:17:11.72,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.86,0:17:13.59,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Commander,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.27,0:17:16.05,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm beginning the mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.93,0:17:18.21,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Mission?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.21,0:17:19.30,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,What mission?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.26,0:17:25.94,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,That is the full story behind Operation Summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.80,0:17:28.44,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask you straight out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.04,0:17:30.16,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,Hana Mutou,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.96,0:17:36.24,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,do you have the skills to complete this \Nmission, and the will to do so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.70,0:17:47.47,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.78,0:18:02.18,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how we do this all this time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.50,0:18:07.94,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It's too big for us to damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.65,0:18:10.61,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's overwhelming them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.35,0:18:13.86,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Capture Hana Mutou!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.19,0:18:34.17,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Is this some kind of nasty dog-monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.18,0:18:42.19,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.99,0:18:51.69,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll deploy a team to find Hana Mutou.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.31,0:18:55.65,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Eliminate Daichi Manatsu and Teppei Arashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.23,0:19:00.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Crush the Intercept Faction's hopes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.64,0:19:07.00,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,High energy readings from \Nunder the nearby sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.66,0:19:11.24,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's surfacing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.24,0:19:12.58,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Could this be...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.67,0:19:18.55,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Get them, Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.21,0:19:54.42,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,The {\i1}Blume{\i0} surfaced?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.72,0:19:58.40,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Is Hana Mutou operating it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.09,0:20:01.49,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.49,0:20:04.22,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you damage the {\i1}Blume{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.96,0:20:58.27,Default,Gu,0000,0000,0000,,It's huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.11,0:21:00.99,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's the {\i1}Blume{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.91,0:21:07.66,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.37,0:21:12.66,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,If you go inside the {\i1}Blume{\i0}, you won't \Nbe able to leave by your own will.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.24,0:21:14.17,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.31,0:21:16.37,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.98,0:21:18.89,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,The captain will come for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.31,0:21:21.31,Default - flashback,D,0000,0000,0000,,I will, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.86,0:21:23.15,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,So it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.86,0:21:28.26,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,Then only Daichi Manatsu can \Nbring you out of the {\i1}Blume{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.26,0:21:30.40,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.39,0:21:32.33,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.41,0:21:35.37,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,If anything happens to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.37,0:21:38.69,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,we'll lose the ability to extricate you from the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.69,0:21:40.86,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,Are you aware of this fact?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.79,0:21:43.23,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.79,0:21:47.20,Default - flashback,P,0000,0000,0000,,And you're all right with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.14,0:21:48.82,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.74,0:21:52.58,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,If I lose the captain,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.76,0:21:55.85,Default - flashback,H,0000,0000,0000,,there'll be no point in leaving the ship anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.93,0:21:58.62,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.01,0:24:16.22,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The spaceship {\i1}Blume{\i0} goes up \Nto the orbiting satellite
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.22,0:24:18.04,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,to rendezvous with the {\i1}Tenkaidou{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.04,0:24:21.39,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,At last, we prepare for the final battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.89,0:24:24.35,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,But what? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.35,0:24:26.94,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,For some reason, the popular idol Ai-chan
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.94,0:24:28.77,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,is here as "governor for a day."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.14,0:24:31.69,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,And Salty Dog is on the move, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.03,0:24:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, on episode 20 of {\i1}Captain Earth{\i0}:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Satellitejack.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:36.62,Title2,,0000,0000,0000,,Satellitejack
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.62,0:24:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Engine, expand!
